  "prompt": "Vayagra medecine tablet is good or not?",
  "response": "Viagra, which contains the active ingredient sildenafil, is a medication used primarily to treat erectile dysfunction (ED) in men. When taken as prescribed by a healthcare professional, it can be effective for improving sexual function and achieving erections. However, it might not be suitable for everyone, and there are potential side effects and contraindications to consider.\n\nHere are some key points regarding the use of Viagra:\n\n1. **Effectiveness**: Many men find Viagra effective in improving their ability to achieve and maintain an erection sufficient for sexual activity.\n\n2. **Mechanism**: Viagra works by relaxing blood vessels and increasing blood flow to the penis during sexual arousal.\n\n3. **Side Effects**: Common side effects include headaches, flushing, upset stomach, and nasal congestion. In rare cases, more serious side effects can occur, such as sudden vision or hearing loss, or an erection lasting more than four hours (priapism), which requires immediate medical attention.\n\n4. **Contraindications**: Viagra should not be used by individuals who take nitrates for chest pain or have serious heart or liver problems. It is important to discuss your complete medical history with a healthcare provider before using Viagra to ensure it is safe for you.\n\n5. **Consultation**: Always consult a healthcare professional before starting Viagra to ensure it is appropriate for your health condition and to receive guidance on its proper use.\n\nIf you have further concerns or questions about using Viagra, a conversation with your doctor would be the most reliable source of personalized information.",
